[I] A tool for managing OCI containers and pods

[T] Podman (the POD MANager) is a tool for managing containers and images,
[T] volumes mounted into those containers, and pods made from groups of
[T] containers.

[U] https://github.com/containers/podman

[A] Red Hat
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/emulator
[F] CROSS NO-LTO

[E] add catatonit conmon netavark

[L] APL
[V] 5.8.2

[D] 304b8a345b59d25c760c80e049c0fab21f609cd976c798bde7092af5 podman-5.8.2.tar.gz https://github.com/containers/podman/archive/v5.8.2/

rungpepinstall=0 rungo=0
. $base/package/*/*/go-conf.in
export CGO_ENABLED=1
var_append GCC_WRAPPER_APPEND ' ' '*cgo*?-O0'
hook_add postmake 5 'mkdir -p $root/etc/containers/'
hook_add postmake 5 'cp -fv ./vendor/go.podman.io/common/pkg/config/containers.conf $root/etc/containers/'
